our boats.

00:02:39,726 --> 00:02:42,162
So what if I told you

00:02:42,162 --> 00:02:45,332
that that kayak
folds out of this?

00:02:46,667 --> 00:02:47,668
Wow.

00:02:47,668 --> 00:02:49,069
WILLIS: So, a few years ago,

00:02:49,069 --> 00:02:50,437
I set out to design a kayak

00:02:50,437 --> 00:02:53,407
that I could literally store
inside my bedroom closet.

00:02:53,407 --> 00:02:55,008
And to do that, I looked back

00:02:55,008 --> 00:02:58,211
to an old childhood passion
Of mine -- Origami.

00:03:01,548 --> 00:03:02,949
Wow!
JOHN: Oh.

00:03:02,949 --> 00:03:04,518
That's pretty clever,
pretty clever.

00:03:04,518 --> 00:03:06,486
So as you can see, the whole
boat unfolds pretty magically

00:03:06,486 --> 00:03:08,522
out of a single, seamless sheet,
just like a piece of paper.

00:03:08,522 --> 00:03:10,891
Now, this material
is extremely durable,

00:03:10,891 --> 00:03:13,427
it's very sturdy,
and it's extremely light.

00:03:13,427 --> 00:03:16,129
The whole boat weighs
only 26 pounds.

00:03:16,129 --> 00:03:20,000
So as you can see, they're
inserting these rigid bulkheads,

00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:21,234
which give the kayak
more structure.

00:03:21,234 --> 00:03:23,870
This orange piece here,

00:03:23,870 --> 00:03:25,706
which was the lid of the case
when I walked in,

00:03:25,706 --> 00:03:28,508
now becomes the floorboard
of the kayak that you sit on.

00:03:28,508 --> 00:03:30,277
Well done.

00:03:30,277 --> 00:03:31,411
They're sealing up
the top seams.

00:03:31,411 --> 00:03:32,746
These are the only seams
in the entire boat.

00:03:32,746 --> 00:03:34,347
They're completely watertight,

00:03:34,347 --> 00:03:37,350
so you're gonna stay dry,
even in rough water.

00:03:37,350 --> 00:03:38,552
So that's a little bit
about how the kayak works.

00:03:38,552 --> 00:03:39,586
I'm gonna hand it to Roberto

00:03:39,586 --> 00:03:41,388
to talk about what you can do
with it.

00:03:41,388 --> 00:03:44,157
Now, sharks, I'm a former
professional paddler,

00:03:44,157 --> 00:03:46,860
and I've tested this
on flat lakes, big ocean waves,

00:03:46,860 --> 00:03:48,195
and even
in Whitewater rapids.

00:03:48,195 --> 00:03:50,097
The Oru Kayak is fast
and durable,

00:03:50,097 --> 00:03:52,966
great for an expert-level
paddler like myself,

00:03:52,966 --> 00:03:54,935
but it's stable,
comfortable, easy to use,

00:03:54,935 --> 00:03:56,503
which is perfect
for beginners.

00:03:56,503 --> 00:03:57,804
